    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-11T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-11T09:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-11T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 11, 1932—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. <persName corresp="#p_GVCM1">Grove</persName> last night made radio speech in
                    which he declared that the Government would deal severely with Communists
                    seeking to overthrow the Government and that the Junta guarantees tranquillity
                    in the country.</p>
                <p>Government agents yesterday afternoon seized about half a million pesos in gold
                    from establishments which had been engaged in buying and selling gold, and
                    payment will be made in local currency for the gold taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
